# Data Structure Consistency Rules

## Critical Principle

**The database schema is the source of truth.** All data structures (backend responses, frontend components, TypeScript types) MUST match the database schema unless transformation is absolutely necessary for display purposes.

---

## Golden Rules

1. **Database schema is authoritative** - All other layers must align with it
2. **Minimize transformations** - Only transform when necessary for display (e.g., date formatting)
3. **Preserve types** - Pass TypeScript types from database → backend → frontend
4. **No wrapper objects** - Don't create unnecessary wrapper objects
5. **Direct mapping** - Map database fields directly to component props

---

## Data Flow

```
Database Schema (Source of Truth)
    ↓
Drizzle schema (`@app/db/schema`) / SQL migrations
    ↓
Backend Response (Route Handlers + `src/server/**`)
    ↓
Frontend Component Props
```

**Each layer should preserve the structure from the previous layer.**

---

## Correct Patterns

### Pattern 1: Direct Data Passing (Recommended)

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Direct data passing from DB query to component
// Database: projects table with fields: id, name, status, createdAt
// Backend: Drizzle row shape matches the table
// Frontend: Uses same structure

// Server Component (illustrative)
import { getDbHttp } from '@app/db';
import { projects } from '@app/db/schema';
import { desc } from 'drizzle-orm';

export default async function ProjectsPage() {
  const db = getDbHttp();
  const rows = await db
    .select()
    .from(projects)
    .orderBy(desc(projects.createdAt))
    .limit(20);

  return <ProjectList projects={rows} />;
}

// Component receives data in database format
interface ProjectListProps {
  projects: Array<{
    id: string;
    name: string;
    status: string;
    createdAt: string; // ISO date string from database
  }>;
}

export function ProjectList({ projects }: ProjectListProps) {
  return (
    <div>
      {projects.map((project) => (
        <div key={project.id}>
          <h3>{project.name}</h3>
          <p>Status: {project.status}</p>
          {/* ✅ GOOD: Format only for display, not in data structure */}
          <p>Created: {formatDate(project.createdAt)}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Pattern 2: Minimal Transformation (Only for Display)

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Transform only for display, keep original data structure
export function ProjectCard({ project }: { project: Project }) {
  // ✅ GOOD: Format date only in render, not in data
  const formattedDate = formatDate(project.createdAt);
  
  // ✅ GOOD: Keep original data structure intact
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>{project.name}</CardTitle>
        <CardDescription>
          Created: {formattedDate} {/* Display formatting only */}
        </CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Badge>{project.status}</Badge>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

### Pattern 3: Using inferred types from Drizzle selects

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Infer row types from `@app/db/schema` + queries
import { projects } from '@app/db/schema';
import type { InferSelectModel } from 'drizzle-orm';

type Project = InferSelectModel<typeof projects>;

export function ProjectList({ projects }: { projects: Project[] }) {
  return <div>{/* ... */}</div>;
}
```

